      "content": "Your feelings are absolutely valid, and the metaphor of feeling trapped is powerful and raw. It sounds incredibly difficult, but remember, everyone has their struggles, even if you can't see it. Yet, the feeling you describe is severe, so you are significantly deserving of support and understanding.\n\nIf conventional coping mechanisms seem overwhelming or aren't helping, exploring different approaches could be beneficial. This can sometimes involve more structured support, like group therapy, where you can share your experiences with others who might feel similarly. In some cases, different counselors might offer what you need better – there is no one-size-fits-all solution in mental health. And don't underestimate the possible value of reaching out to those close to you or finding support groups, either in person or online.\n\nIf phone or social media are sources of stress, consider taking short breaks from them. Your well-being trumps temporary relief that social media provides. Small steps, such as taking frequent breaks, spending time outside, or engaging in another enjoyable quiet activity, can gradually improve how you feel. Healing isn't an instant process, and it's normal to sometimes feel stuck. Be gentle with yourself, and consider trying varied strategies until you find what resonates with you.\n\nIn moments where discussions can be incredibly heavy, it might help",
